possible_values: A1: Covert Development.  May be combined or corroborated with other intelligence but action cannot be taken directly. Permission must be sought from the originator
A2: Covert Use. Covert action may be taken on this intelligence although the source or techniques must be protected. May not be used in isolation as evidence
A3: Overt Use. Overt action is permitted on this intelligence.  See additional notes for what this information can be used for.
S1. Delegate Authority. The originator of the intelligence DOES PERMIT the unsupervised sanitisation of the material in order to allow dissemination to a wider audience
S2. Consult Originator. The originator of the intelligence DOES NOT PERMIT the sanitisation of the material for a wider dissemination without consultation being sought
